and let me &s;earch in my own brea&s;t for that
peace and contentment, which I have not been
able to find in all the &s;cenes of my &s;ucce&s;s. In
being detached from the world, I &s;hall be deli|vered
from folly and ingratitude, as well as ex|empted
from an expence, which I &s;hould have
found it very difficult, if not impracticable, to
&s;upport; I &s;hall have little or no temptation to
mi&s;pend my time, and more undi&s;turbed oppor|tunity
