<PB N="154" REF="160">
on which they may exerci&s;e them&s;elves in walk|ing,
&s;kittles, bowls, and variety of other diver|&s;ions,
according to the inclination of each.</P>
<P>Our adventurer being admitted a denizen of
this community, found him&s;elf bewildered in the
mid&s;t of &s;trangers, who, by their appearance,
did not at all prepo&s;&s;e&s;s him in their favour; and
